{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida80274ea-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"710a"},"text":"§ 710a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Parental leave for members of certain reserve components of the armed forces","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida80274eb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274ec-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Under regulations prescribed by the Secretary of Defense, a member of a reserve component of the armed forces described in subsection (b) is allowed parental leave for a duration of up to 12 inactive-duty training periods, under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s206"},"text":"section 206 of title 37","children":[],"tail":", during the one-year period beginning after the following events:"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274ed-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the birth or adoption of a child of the member and to care for such child; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274ee-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the placement of a minor child with the member for adoption or long-term foster care.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274ef-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary concerned, under uniform regulations to be prescribed by the Secretary of Defense, may authorize leave described under paragraph (1) to be taken after the one-year period described in paragraph (1) in the case of a member described in subsection (b) who, except for this subparagraph, would lose unused parental leave at the end of the one-year period described in paragraph (1) as a result of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/2/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" operational requirements;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/2/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" professional military education obligations; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/2/A/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other circumstances that the Secretary determines reasonable and appropriate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The regulations prescribed under subparagraph (A) shall require that any leave authorized to be taken after the one-year period described in paragraph (1) shall be taken within a reasonable period of time, as determined by the Secretary of Defense, after cessation of the circumstances warranting the extended deadline.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A member described in this subsection is a member of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the selected reserve who is entitled to compensation under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s206"},"text":"section 206 of title 37","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s710a/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the individual ready reserve who is entitled to compensation under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s206"},"text":"section 206 of title 37","children":[],"tail":" when attending or participating in a sufficient number of periods of inactive-duty training during a year to count the year as a qualifying year of creditable service toward eligibility for retired pay."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida80274f8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/31/dA/tVI/s601/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–31, div. A, title VI, § 601(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 2023","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/137/288"},"text":"137 Stat. 288","children":[],"tail":", § 711; renumbered 710a and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/dA/tVI/s603/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, div. A, title VI, § 603(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/1931"},"text":"138 Stat. 1931","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dA/tXVII/s1701/a/10"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. A, title XVII, § 1701(a)(10)","children":[],"tail":", (11), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1208"},"text":"139 Stat. 1208","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida80274f9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida80274fa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida80274fb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s1701/a/10"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 1701(a)(10)","children":[],"tail":", made amendment identical to that made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/s603/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, § 603(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":". See 2024 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s1701/a/11/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 1701(a)(11)(A)","children":[],"tail":", made amendment identical to that made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/s603/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, § 603(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":". See 2024 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s1701/a/11/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 1701(a)(11)(B)","children":[],"tail":", made amendments identical to that made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/s603/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, § 603(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (B). See 2024 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2024—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/s603/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, § 603(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s711"},"text":"section 711 of this title","children":[],"tail":" relating to parental leave for members of certain reserve components of the armed forces as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/s603/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, § 603(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “paragraph (1)” for “subparagraph (A)” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/s603/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, § 603(b)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “subparagraph (A)” for “clause (i)” and a period for “.;” at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/s603/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, § 603(a)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “is a member of the Army, Navy, Marine Corps, Air Force, or Space Force who” after “described in this subsection” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida80274fc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida80274fd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2024 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/159/dA/tVI/s603/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–159, div. A, title VI, § 603(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/1931"},"text":"138 Stat. 1931","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/118/159/dA/tVI/s603/c"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending and renumbering this section] shall take effect on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 2025","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"ida80274fe-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/31/dA/tVI/s601/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–31, div. A, title VI, § 601(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 2023","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/137/289"},"text":"137 Stat. 289","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/118/31/dA/tVI/s601/e"},"text":"“This section [enacting this section and amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12732"},"text":"section 12732 of this title","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s206"},"text":"section 206 of Title 37","children":[],"tail":", Pay and Allowances of the Uniformed Services, and provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12732"},"text":"section 12732 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] and the amendments made by this section shall take effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 2024","children":[],"tail":", and apply with respect to periods of parental leave that commence on or after such date.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
